# Bounded contexts (modular monolith)

Single Maven module; logical boundaries in `dev.vepo.cursos.*`. Full table: [docs/domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) §Bounded contexts.

## Context map

| Context | Packages |
|---------|----------|
| Platform | `infra` |
| Identity & auth facade | `auth`, `identity` |
| Catalog | `catalog` |
| Course authoring | `course`, `category` |
| Enrollment | `enrollment` |
| Progress | `progress` |
| Git sync | `git` |
| Email | `mailer` |

## Dependency rules

- Feature packages **may depend on** packages listed in the domain spec for that row.
- **`infra`** must not contain domain logic — only cross-cutting HTTP, errors, Passport client, SPA routing, and dev setup.
- **`..*Repository`** must not depend on `..*Endpoint`.
- Cross-context reactions use services in the owning context — not direct repository access across unrelated packages.

## Enforcement

`ArchitectureTest` enforces Request/Response naming, `@DenyAll` on endpoints, one HTTP method per endpoint, and `EntityManager` confinement.

## When adding a feature

1. Complete [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc) — feature analysis, task break, user approval.
2. Place code in the correct context package.
3. Update domain spec if new vocabulary.
